The Wet Whistle Co.. The Wet Whistle Co. is not a new coffee… | by Christopher Sciortino | Spill Them Beans | Medium Sitemap Open in app Sign up Sign in Medium Logo Write Sign up Sign in Spill Them Beans · Coffee shops are rich, full-bodied cups of community. Here, we tell the caffeine-fueled stories of humor & humanity that we’ve witnessed in the writer’s favorite environment. Open for submissions! See the pinned post for guidelines. The Wet Whistle Co. Christopher Sciortino 3 min read · Jan 21, 2024 -- 1 Listen Share The Wet Whistle Co. is not a new coffee shop to me in the slightest. Since the beginning of my Sophomore year in college, The Wet Whistle Co. has been one of my all-time favorite places to study and crank out homework each and every time. From the staff to the themes, and of course, the coffee, another day at The Wet Whistle Co. has me ready for work and brings a comfortable feeling to settle down. For some context, I have always fancied the idea of visiting coffee shops and cafes since my Freshman year in college. The idea that I could unwind whether in a local establishment meant for some light-weighted work was always fascinating to me. Even the music was a core feature of cafes as I was always a fan of jazz music during my studies and coffee shops only made such music all the more enjoyable. Nonetheless, The Wet Whistle Co. leaves me to believe that this is the best coffee shop I could visit no matter the occasion. Press enter or click to view image in full size The Wet Whistle Co. Upon entering The Wet Whistle Co. I am greeted by one of their common themes as well as mascot, the skeleton. The Wet Whistle Co. gives off a unique theme of “life and death,” nothing too symbolic but something to think about nonetheless. Their walls alternate from green to purple, creating a very enchanting atmosphere with simple, yet stylish furniture to comfort their guests. Everywhere you look, The Wet Whistle Co. decorates its surroundings with unique liquor brands they wish to advertise to appropriate customers. I appreciate the aesthetic The Wet Whistle Co. offers and always find myself intrigued with how they present the layout of the store. As for The Wet Whistle Co.’s staff, they feature a lively group of people behind the counter always engaging in conversation. Their apparel is vibrant and casual, as well as complements the theme of their brand. Who I would assume is the manager for The Wet Whistle Co. is a very cheerful woman who does not seem to forget a face. Even after a full two months upon returning from the Winter Break, she recognized me and even remembered which university I belonged to in the area. I always feel very welcomed after interacting with any staff at The Wet Whistle Co. and am reminded of their constant hospitality as their staff checks up on their customers every once and a while. To save the best for last, today’s visit at The Wet Whistle Co. offers a variety of Valentine’s Day-themed beverages as well as their standard coffee brews. From coffees to teas to even milkshakes, The Wet Whistle Co. details its menu on three, colorful chalkboards that bring out some originality in their drinks. They even assort subtle pastries across the counter, grabbing the attention of hungry customers like myself and adding to the variety of their menu. Today I decided to give a shot to their Valentine’s Day menu and energize myself with some caffeine as I attend to some projects assigned to me for the week. In all, I will always appreciate how comforting it is to visit The Wet Whistle Co. and be greeted by their amazing staff. I look forward to many more opportunities that await me, potentially stumbling across a new menu theme every once in a while. However, what I look forward to the most is seeing that skeleton by the counter, enjoying a cup of coffee just like me. Who: A curious college student. Where: Archdale in downtown High Point, North Carolina. When: An early Saturday evening. What: Mr. Sandman (Honey and Vanilla Latte). Privacy Policy - Marketing Website Version: 9-2-2021 Data collected on the basis of consent Upon your request and expression of consent, we collect the following data for the purpose of marketing to you. Your data is not used for any other purposes or shared with third parties. It is removed upon your withdrawal of consent or your request to stop being marketed to. Contact Information Email address, first name, last name, company name, and a description of how Whistle can help you: this data is collected when you fill out and submit the contact form displayed throughout the Website. The contact information is transmitted and stored in our contact management system so that we can keep track of our interactions (email, meeting notes, downloading resources from our website) over time. Periodically we will send product updates, policy changes or other information we feel is relevant to our clients or potential clients.  These updates are typically sent via email.  People receiving these emails can opt out of additional communication at any time. Retention period: the aforementioned data is retained indefinitely so we can continue to market to you according to our content and marketing strategy. Data collected on the basis of legitimate interest Based on our legitimate interests , we collect the following data for the purpose of running this website. Your data is not used for any other purposes or shared with third parties. It is removed upon your request. Statistics The website uses a minimal build of Google Analytics, a service which transmits website traffic data to Google Analytics servers in the United States and allows us to notice trends to improve the user experience on our website. This minimal build processes personal data such as: the unique User ID set by Google Analytics, the date and time, the title of the page being viewed, the URL of the page being viewed, the URL of the page that was viewed prior to the current page, the screen resolution, the time in local timezone, the files that were clicked on and downloaded, the links clicked on to an outside domain, the type of device, and the country, region, and city. You may opt out of this tracking at any time by activating the “Do Not Track” setting in your browser. Embedded content from other websites Articles on the Website may include embedded content (e.g. videos, charts, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor had visited the other website. These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracing your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website. Your rights pertaining your data If you have filled out the contact form on this Website, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we rectify or erase any personal data we hold about you. The District provides service to the cities of Lakewood and University Place as well as the Town of Steilacoom. About Us Where We're Located There are six fire stations strategically located throughout the fire district and operate 24 hours per day, seven days per week. The fleet includes six engines, one ladder truck, five medic units and two Battalion Chiefs.  In addition, three marine boats and one brush engine are cross-staffed when needed for emergency response. Our Stations Serving Our Community The West Pierce Emergency Management Coalition includes West Pierce Fire & Rescue, the cities of Lakewood and University Place, and the Town of Steilacoom to serve the communities efficiently and effectively should a large-scale emergency happen.
